The sauce is legit amazing, esp when you dip the duck in their sambal‚Äîomg chef‚Äôs kiss.

Tried the roast pork too, and it‚Äôs a great combo: crackly skin and tender meat. Only prob is it gets busy, so be ready to queue a bit, but SO worth it!!

This store sets the gold standard for dining experiences. The staff is  warm and genuinely attentive making every visit a pleasure. The food is delicious and consistently excellent. In an era where great service is rare, this place exceeds expectations in every way.

A must-visit for anyone who appreciates  quality food paired with impeccable service. Highly recommended‚ÄîI‚Äôll definitely be back.

Came here to try the wanton mee and and added a roast duck leg. Noodles were good!

On the sweeter side with an old school taste I remembered from the 90s. I enjoyed the noodles and charsiew. Roast duck was not bad too!

Price point is definitely good. It was still below $10. Hard to get roast duck leg without losing an arm and leg these days.

One of the best so far!
Their sambal chilli also very nice too!
Worth my time to drop by here!

Tried the Char Siew Roast Pork Rice ($4) and Roasted Duck Noodles ($4). All taste nice, especially like the roast pork with it's tender fats and crispy skin. Noodles were so tasty with the sauce. Chilli was good too. Good portions and value for money. Would recommend üëç
